ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Site
Notes: Study Site

ElementDescription: Visit name
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer I wanted to be friends with on a social networking site (i.e., MySpace, Facebook) ignored my friend request.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer removed me from his/her list of friends on a social networking site.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer made me feel bad by not listing me in his/her ''Top 8'' or ''Top Friends'' list.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer posted mean things about me on a public portion of a social networking site (SNS).
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer posted pictures of me on a SNS that made me look bad.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer spread rumors about me or revealed secrets I had told them using public posts on a SNS.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer sent me a mean message on a SNS.
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer pretended to be me on a SNS and did things to make me look bad/damage my friendships
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: I found out that I was excluded from a party or social event over a SNS (i.e., MySpace, Facebook)
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: Past 2 months: A peer made me feel jealous by ''messing'' with my girlfriend/boyfriend on a SNS (i.e., posting pictures together, writing messages on a Facebook wall, ranking him/her in a ''Top 8'' or ''Top Friends'').
Notes: 1= Never; 5= A few times a week; 99= Missing
